.TH "device_prepare" 9 "device_prepare" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
device_prepare \- Prepare a device for system power transition.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" device_prepare
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "pm_message_t state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Device to handle.
.IP "state" 12
PM transition of the system being carried out.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Execute the ->\fBprepare\fP callback(s) for given device.  No new children of the
device may be registered after this function has returned.
